Selling a Swiss K31 w/ 440 rounds of GP11 ammo.

Gun is in fantastic condition.  Bluing is excellent along with all mechanical aspects of the gun.  In my personal opinion, this is the finest bolt action rifle made during the WWII era, the best part is, they never saw actual combat.  I have only shot 40 rounds through this gun, and let me say its extremely accurate.  Im not a slouch with irons, but bench shooting from a front rest 1 1/2" groups are easy.  I put this gun on a sled and could get 3 shot groups under 1".  The triggers on these are super smooth and light, very precise, as all swiss made products are. 

I'm including 440 rounds of the surplus GP11 ammo.  Its berdan primed, brass cased and  NON CORROSIVE!  Aside from a VERY solid handload, it doesn't get any better than this.

I love this rifle, but I have my eye on other things, and since I rarely shoot it, I figure someone else might enjoy it more.  These guns and ammo are getting hard to come by, especially in this condition, don't miss out on a great package deal.

$550 or best offer.  No trades please.  Thank you.
